race.description: Tabtouch Honouring Jockeys Past And Present Handicap
race.comment: BRAZEN BID (3) was put aside and changed stables after a couple of modest efforts on wet tracks earlier in the season. All of his form has been fresh up, and on a firmer track at an easier level, he should be hard to hold out, especially if the money comes for him. CRUISE TO RIO (1) ran a much better race when runner-up here 9 days ago in only her second run from the local Tim Stone stable. She is still on the up, and her met win is not far away. EL FOXIE (4) won his maiden here in his penultimate run, and then had no luck on this track last time out when trapped wide throughout. He can make amends, even from the wide draw. OUR EXISTENCE (6) was beaten by a wide gate at Ascot last start, after finishing an encouraging fifth here before that. William Pike steps into the irons, and the pair merits healthy respect. GASPARDO (8) made up some late ground when finishing third here a month ago. He has a good draw, and another solid effort can be expected.
